<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1568,2026]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
This is a new record for 
<collectingCountry box="[417,512,1568,1594]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[528,594,1568,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,960,982]" captionTargetBox="[354,1230,200,919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@1.[340,1247,187,933]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Map of the Horn of Africa region, showing the distribution of Cystostemon heliocharis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5308329" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5308329/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The previously unidentified material was included among specimens sent from the South East Rangelands project in 
<collectingCountry box="[625,720,1604,1630]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
to UPS. The collection was made in open shrubland on a northfacing slope of a stony hill.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1568,2026]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Balfour (1884: 82)" authorityName="Balfour" authorityPageNumber="82" authorityYear="1884" box="[316,681,1676,1702]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[316,459,1676,1702]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Cystostemon</emphasis>
Balfour (1884: 82)
</taxonomicName>
was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H." box="[869,1124,1676,1702]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref2845" refString="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H. (1982) A revision of Cystostemon Balf. f. (Boraginaceae). Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 40: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1982">Miller &amp; Riedl (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, who recognized 13 species, distributed from the southwestern Arabian Peninsula and 
<collectingCountry box="[797,883,1712,1738]" name="Yemen" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Socotra</collectingCountry>
in the north, to 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1159,1712,1738]" name="Zambia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1217,1299,1712,1738]" name="Angola" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Angola</collectingCountry>
in the south. Since then, three further species have been described from 
<collectingCountry box="[795,877,1748,1774]" name="Angola" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Angola</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[932,1018,1748,1774]" name="Zambia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Zambia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, E. S." box="[1060,1234,1748,1774]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref2768" refString="Martins, E. S. (1988 a) Cystostemon loveridgei E. S. Martins and C. mwinilungensis E. S. Martins. Garcia de Orta, Serie de Botanica 9 (1 - 2): 75." type="journal article" year="1988">Martins (1988a</bibRefCitation>
, b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1568,2026]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H." box="[189,434,1784,1810]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref2845" refString="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H. (1982) A revision of Cystostemon Balf. f. (Boraginaceae). Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 40: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1982">Miller &amp; Riedl (1982)</bibRefCitation>
cited material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. G. Mill. &amp; Riedl" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="S. Moore" box="[628,903,1784,1810]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heliocharis">
<emphasis box="[628,903,1784,1810]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Cystostemon heliocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[968,1046,1785,1811]" name="Yemen" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Yemen</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1099,1194,1784,1810]" name="Somalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, and provided a map of the distribution of the species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Thulin, M." box="[479,648,1820,1847]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="53 - 54" refId="ref3401" refString="Thulin, M. (2006 a) Cystostemon. In: Thulin, M. (Ed.) Flora of Somalia, vol. 3. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, pp. 53 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2006">Thulin (2006a)</bibRefCitation>
treated four species, 
<emphasis box="[886,1051,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. G. Mill. &amp; Riedl" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="S. Moore" box="[886,1047,1820,1846]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heliocharis">C. heliocharis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Miller &amp; Riedl (1982: 11)" authorityName="Miller &amp; Riedl" authorityPageNumber="11" authorityYear="1982" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intricatus">
<emphasis box="[1058,1198,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">C. intricatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H." pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref2845" refString="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H. (1982) A revision of Cystostemon Balf. f. (Boraginaceae). Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 40: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1982">Miller &amp; Riedl (1982: 11)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Miller &amp; Riedl (1982: 8)" authorityName="Miller &amp; Riedl" authorityPageNumber="8" authorityYear="1982" box="[186,633,1856,1882]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[186,349,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">C. somaliensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H." box="[356,633,1856,1882]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref2845" refString="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H. (1982) A revision of Cystostemon Balf. f. (Boraginaceae). Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 40: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1982">Miller &amp; Riedl (1982: 8)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Miller &amp; Riedl (1982: 15)" authorityName="Miller &amp; Riedl" authorityPageNumber="15" authorityYear="1982" box="[692,1124,1856,1883]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis box="[692,827,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">C. virescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H." box="[834,1124,1856,1883]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref2845" refString="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H. (1982) A revision of Cystostemon Balf. f. (Boraginaceae). Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 40: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1982">Miller &amp; Riedl (1982: 15)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in Flora of 
<collectingCountry box="[1254,1349,1856,1882]" name="Somalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="Riedl, H. &amp; Edwards, S." box="[136,420,1892,1919]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="64 - 102" refId="ref3104" refString="Riedl, H. &amp; Edwards, S. (2006) Boraginaceae. In: Hedberg, I., Ensermu Kelbessa, Edwards, S. &amp; Sebsebe Demissew (Eds.) Flora of Ethiopia and Eritrea, vol. 5. The National Herbarium, Addis Ababa and Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala, pp. 64 - 102." type="book chapter" year="2006">Riedl &amp; Edwards (2006)</bibRefCitation>
recorded two species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Miller &amp; Riedl (1982: 12)" authorityName="Miller &amp; Riedl" authorityPageNumber="12" authorityYear="1982" box="[686,1147,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ethiopicus">
<emphasis box="[686,836,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">C. ethiopicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H." box="[846,1147,1892,1918]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref2845" refString="Miller, A. G. &amp; Riedl, H. (1982) A revision of Cystostemon Balf. f. (Boraginaceae). Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 40: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1982">Miller &amp; Riedl (1982: 12)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller &amp; Riedl" authorityYear="1982" box="[1206,1344,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis box="[1206,1344,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">C. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in Flora of 
<collectingCountry box="[168,263,1928,1954]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[320,400,1928,1954]" name="Eritrea" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
. The revised map for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. G. Mill. &amp; Riedl" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="S. Moore" box="[650,810,1928,1954]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cystostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heliocharis">
<emphasis box="[650,810,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">C. heliocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[827,893,1928,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,960,982]" captionTargetBox="[354,1230,200,919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@1.[340,1247,187,933]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Map of the Horn of Africa region, showing the distribution of Cystostemon heliocharis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5308329" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5308329/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) shows that the new Ethiopian record is in close vicinity of localities in northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[557,649,1964,1990]" name="Somalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Somalia</collectingCountry>
(Somaliland). A photograph of a plant from a locality in northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[136,228,2000,2026]" name="Somalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Somalia</collectingCountry>
is shown in 
<figureCitation box="[369,438,2000,2026]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1598,1620]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,1008,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-39@1.[340,1247,1008,1574]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cystostemon heliocharis, from northwestern Somalia (Somaliland), ca. 120 km from Erigavo to Burao, 18 Aug 2019. Photograph by Boris Vrškový." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5308333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5308333/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
